00:00:04.674 --> 00:00:10.495
today ill show you how i did this super easy summer bronze makeup.

00:00:11.986 --> 00:00:18.809
and i used only this eyeshadow quad by MAC and 
 only 1 angled brush!! so please keep on watching.

00:00:20.229 --> 00:00:23.035
alright. so ill start with this quad which i bought several years ago.

00:00:24.263 --> 00:00:29.522
you dont have to use the exact same colors. if 
 u have 4 different browns, try them too.

00:00:30.572 --> 00:00:39.650
and for a brush, i use this Sigma SS275 
 which is a bit fluffy angled one.

00:00:40.343 --> 00:00:50.454
usually, i use this brush for nose contouring or highlighting but 
 today ill use only this brush for eye makeup.

00:00:52.208 --> 00:00:54.765
firstly i take this bronze color.

00:00:57.738 --> 00:01:01.738
then apply it on the lid.

00:01:06.075 --> 00:01:10.888
if you want a natural look, dont go blend upwards too much.

00:01:19.639 --> 00:01:25.508
should look like this. and dont forget to blend out the lines.

00:01:28.276 --> 00:01:32.244
and everytime you change the color, wipe the color off on the tissue paper.

00:01:36.740 --> 00:01:46.550
then take the lightest color on the tip of the 
 brush and apply it on the bottom lashline.

00:01:50.422 --> 00:02:00.530
after that, take the darkest color on the tip of the brush 
 and apply it along the lashline and on the outer corner.

00:02:16.189 --> 00:02:22.670
the angle of this brush fits perfectly on the 
 curve so its really easy to apply colors.

00:02:24.859 --> 00:02:29.870
i just happened to use this brush one day and since 
 then, im doing this look all the time now.

00:02:33.077 --> 00:02:46.820
and the last one which is kinda optional but apply this bright 
 orange color on the middle of the lid with your finger.

00:02:48.596 --> 00:02:50.380
it will add the dimension to your eyes.

00:02:54.734 --> 00:03:00.690
for the lips, ill use this revlon l/s #205. (i already applied mascara.)

00:03:01.482 --> 00:03:03.680
it has some gold shimmer in it.

00:03:14.618 --> 00:03:16.560
now the make up is done.

00:03:18.397 --> 00:03:21.100
i think this fits this super hot summer.

00:03:21.941 --> 00:03:26.620
